ocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bnm1665702916682.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bnm1665702916682.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bnm1665702916682.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bnm1665702916682\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Log off from the DBMS.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__section_wck_mpw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499054e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__p_d130244e1_d130245e1_d130246e1\">Log off from the DBMS for the current logon path.\n        Update the number of open files and open cursors. If the DBMS does not support Logoff,\n        return 0 to Uniface. If Logoff was successful, return 0 to Uniface, otherwise return -3.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__p_d130247e1_d130248e1_d130249e1\">Connectors that are TM-controlled\n          (<code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;TMEnabled=1</code>) should perform the standard cleanup and internal\n        administration, but the connector must not disconnect from the DBMS.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__section_uvm_mkx_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499054e65\">From Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Preconditions realized by Uniface—There is a current logon path. All tables for the current\n        logon path are closed.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Available from Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrvini</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__2\">Unique identification of the current logon\n                path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;iobuf</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__2\">Points to the general I/O buffer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;sqlbuf</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__2\">Points to the SQL buffer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;TMEnabled</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1__entry__2\">Indicates whether the connector is\n                TM-controlled.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__section_vmb_nkx_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499054e146\">To Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Connector request return values related to the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Logoff</code> request.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Request Return Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__2\">Logoff was successful.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__1\">-3</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__2\">Exceptional error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__1\">-16</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bnm1665702916682__table_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1__entry__2\">DBMS reported network error.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__p_d130259e1_d130260e1_d130261e1\">If the connector request return value is less than 0,\n        an error code must be supplied in <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__section_kcr_qpw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499054e219\">Service functions</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__ul_ffq_rpw_fwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__li_d46745e1_d46746e1_d46747e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prf1665702918304.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prf1665702918304.html\" title=\"Return the number of open operating system files.\">udfilcnt</a>— Update the number\n          of open files. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__li_d46748e1_d46749e1_d46750e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sou1665702918447.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sou1665702918447.html\" title=\"Return a number that uniquely identifies the current logon path.\">udpathset</a>— Provide Uniface\n          with a number that uniquely identifies the created logon path. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__li_d46751e1_d46752e1_d46753e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fjd1665702918235.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fjd1665702918235.html\" title=\"Return the number of open database cursors.\">udcurscnt</a>— Update the number\n          of open cursors. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__section_byw_4pw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499054e255\">Extra information</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__p_d130268e1_d130269e1_d130270e1\">The Logoff request is provided with a dummy control\n        block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not have an associated\n        connector workspace.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__p_d130271e1_d130272e1_d130273e1\">When Logoff is requested, the transaction on the\n        current logon path has usually been committed or rolled back. This is not guaranteed,\n        however, since transactions are defined by the ProcScript programmer, not by Uniface.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__p_d130274e1_d130275e1_d130276e1\">If the corresponding Logon request created an entry in\n        the connector’s logon handle table, that entry must be cleared.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__note_yjg_qpw_fwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The connector cannot decide to commit or roll back\n        changes to or from the DBMS under any circumstances. This is the responsibility of the\n        application running under Uniface.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__section_ivh_spw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499054e274\">TM-Controlled Connectors</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bnm1665702916682__p_d130280e1_d130281e1_d130282e1\">TM-controlled connectors are not allowed to begin,\n        commit, or rollback transactions. For more information on <code class=\"ph codeph\">Logoff</code> and\n        TM-controlled DBMS connectors, see the \"Data Structures\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jkq1665702915666.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Structures</a><p>Information is exchanged between Uniface and the connector by means of a set of data structures defined by Uniface. The connector must conform to the semantics of the data structures and the associated protocols.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azl1665702915888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uctrl</a><p>Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526145\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Logoff ('A') Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Log off from the DBMS. Description Log off from the DBMS for the current logon path. Update the number of open files and open cursors. If the DBMS does not support Logoff, return 0 to Uniface. If Logoff was successful, return 0 to Uniface, otherwise return -3. Connectors that are TM-controlled ( uctrl->TMEnabled=1 ) should perform the standard cleanup and internal administration, but the connector must not disconnect from the DBMS. From Uniface Preconditions realized by Uniface—There is a current logon path. All tables for the current logon path are closed. Table 1. Information Available from Uniface Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->udrvini Unique identification of the current logon path. uctrl->iobuf Points to the general I/O buffer. uctrl->sqlbuf Points to the SQL buffer. uctrl->TMEnabled Indicates whether the connector is TM-controlled. To Uniface Connector request return values related to the Logoff request. Table 2. Connector Request Return Values Value Description 0 Logoff was successful. -3 Exceptional error. -16 DBMS reported network error. If the connector request return value is less than 0, an error code must be supplied in uctrl->udrverr . Service functions udfilcnt — Update the number of open files. udpathset — Provide Uniface with a number that uniquely identifies the created logon path. udcurscnt — Update the number of open cursors. Extra information The Logoff request is provided with a dummy control block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not have an associated connector workspace. When Logoff is requested, the transaction on the current logon path has usually been committed or rolled back. This is not guaranteed, however, since transactions are defined by the ProcScript programmer, not by Uniface. If the corresponding Logon request created an entry in the connector’s logon handle table, that entry must be cleared. CAUTION: The connector cannot decide to commit or roll back changes to or from the DBMS under any circumstances. This is the responsibility of the application running under Uniface. TM-Controlled Connectors TM-controlled connectors are not allowed to begin, commit, or rollback transactions. For more information on Logoff and TM-controlled DBMS connectors, see the \"Data Structures\" topic. Related Links Data Structures Information is exchanged between Uniface and the connector by means of a set of data structures defined by Uniface. The connector must conform to the semantics of the data structures and the associated protocols. uctrl Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}